The paper discusses energy efficiency in cloud and distributed computing systems, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The use of sensors and their communication with a processing unit suggests a focus on Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The need for appropriate commands from the processing unit implies a consideration of System and Control (cs.SY). The use of battery and solar cells suggests a focus on Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Embedded Systems (cs.ET) for efficient power management.
